{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incomplete SIB2 configuration in phy_config_update_sib2_request\n\n### Summary\nThe `phy_config_update_sib2_request` function in `openair1/PHY/INIT/lte_init.c` was only partially implemented, configuring only MBSFN parameters but missing all other SIB2-related PHY configuration. This caused unexpected behavior when SIB2 updates were processed, as critical uplink and downlink parameters were not being updated.\n\nThe function now properly configures all SIB2-related parameters including PUCCH, PDSCH, PUSCH configurations, SRS parameters, and FeMBMS settings, matching the complete SIB2 configuration done during initial PHY setup.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/INIT/lte_init.c`: Enhanced `phy_config_update_sib2_request` to configure all SIB2-related parameters\n"
}